text: Kingston (formerly Appletree Cove Washington Place Names) is a census- designated place (CDP) in Kitsap County, Washington, United States. The population was 2,515 at the 2020 census. Kingston is near the shores of Appletree Cove and the Puget Sound. It is home to a major Washington State Ferry linking it to Edmonds. ==References== Category:Census-designated places in Washington (state)
title: Kingston, Washington
